pl.softfly.integ.shipment.out

Class TransformOutgoingShipmentBean

  • java.lang.Object
    • pl.softfly.integ.shipment.out.OutgoingShipmentBean
      • pl.softfly.integ.shipment.out.TransformOutgoingShipmentBean
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OutgoingShipment

    public class TransformOutgoingShipmentBean
extends OutgoingShipmentBean
    Determine the outgoing shipment (endpoints, recipient) to which the document should be sent.
    1. Call OutgoingShipmentBean.isRequired(pl.softfly.integ.doc.entity.DocumentHeader).
    2. Call OutgoingShipmentBean.determine(pl.softfly.integ.doc.entity.DocumentHeader).
    3. Send shipments by SenderEndpoint.
    4. Call again "isRequired" to check if shipments have been sent correctly.
      If you correctly end the use case,
      otherwise try to determine the next shipments using other endpoints, try again after the timeout in step 2.
    Author:
    Grzegorz Ziemski
